[1] Cases in various countries
Asia
---
Sri Lanka
- National. 17 Jul 2017. The number of dengue fever cases in Sri Lanka is up significantly in 2017, in fact, it is 3.5 times more than the average number of cases for the same period between 2010 and 2016. Through [17 Jul 2017], the Ministry of Health reports 93 322 dengue cases, including 250 deaths to date.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/sri-lanka-dengue-cases-3-12-times-higher-5-year-average-69979/

- National. 13 Jul 2017. The number of dengue fever cases in Sri Lanka continue to mount as some 10 000 additional cases have been reported in the past week. Through Wed 12 Jul 2017, the country case count climbed to 89 885, up from 80 000 last [Thu 6 Jul 2017]. In the capital city of Colombo, the cases have topped 20 000 as of 13 Jul 2017, by far the most of any district in the country. In December 2015, Sanofi Pasteur, the vaccines division of Sanofi announced the 1st country (Mexico) to approve their dengue vaccine, Dengvaxia. Since then, some 17 countries have approved the vaccine. However, in Sri Lanka, officials say more research is required prior to introduction into the population.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/colombo-dengue-cases-top-20000-vaccine-requires-more-research-92273/

- National. 6 Jul 2017. Following flooding, Sri Lanka experiences worst-ever dengue outbreak; at least 225 dead, 76 000 infected (Mallawarachi, 7/4). CNN: Deadly dengue fever outbreak kills hundreds in Sri Lanka "...Experts worry the death toll could yet increase, as the country's health infrastructure struggles to cope with the virus' rapid spread. 'Dengue will get worse as ...
http://www.kff.org/news-summary/following-flooding-sri-lanka-experiences-worst-ever-dengue-outbreak-at-least-225-dead-76k-infected/

- National. 3 Jul 2017. According to the latest figures obtained from the health sector, 71 000 cases of dengue have been reported from across the country. A total of 226 people lost their lives owing to dengue during the past 6 months. 658 dengue patients are currently receiving in-house treatment at the special dengue treatment centre at the Negombo District Hospital.
http://newsfirst.lk/english/2017/07/71000-cases-dengue-reported-across-island/169809

- National. 30 Jun 2017. Through [30 Jun 2017], the Sri Lanka Epidemiology Unit with the Ministry of Health puts the dengue tally at 71 298, including 215 fatalities. This compares with 55 150, including 78 deaths in all of 2016. 80 students at the University of Moratuwa have reportedly contracted dengue fever prompting the temporary closure of the school.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/sri-lanka-dengue-crisis-military-troops-deployed-university-moratuwa-closed-26929/

- National. 20 Jun 2017. 63 987 affected by virus with at least 200 deaths. Tremendous rise in DEN type 2
http://famagusta-gazette.com/sri-lanka-dengue-epidemic-people-affected-by-the-virus-p40879-69.htm

[Maps of Sri Lanka can be seen at http://geology.com/world/sri-lanka-map.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,144. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Bhutan
- National. 14 Jul 2017. More than 100 cases reported since last month [June 2017]. Phuentsholing hospital 33 dengue fever cases; Samtse hospital 46; and Samdrupjongkhar hospital, 42 cases as of yesterday [13 Jul 2017].
http://www.kuenselonline.com/dengue-fever-outbreak-in-three-dzongkhags/

[Maps of Bhutan can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/bhutan/maps/bhutan-political-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,154. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

India
- National. 15 Jul 2017. In just 3 years, dengue cases in India have increased by 280 percent
http://www.downtoearth.org.in/news/390-per-cent-increase-in-chikungunya-cases-despite-rise-in-vector-borne-diseases-58283

- Assam. 19 Jun 2017. India 49 deaths [as of 31 May 2017]. In 2016 a total of 6157 dengue cases were reported in the state, which is an all-time record and 7 people had lost their lives till 2016. The capital Guwahati is one of the worst dengue-affected cities of Assam.
https://www.northeasttoday.in/dengue-strikes-assam-49-cases-reported/

- Delhi. 10 Jul 2017. A total of 109 cases of dengue have been reported in Delhi this year [2017]. According to the weekly report by the MCD [Municipal Corporation of Delhi], a total of 60 cases of the disease were reported from Delhi, while 49 were reported from outside the state. 33 cases were reported from the North MCD, while 36 cases were reported from South MCD, and 18 from East MCD. No deaths from the disease have been reported so far.
https://news.webindia123.com/news/Articles/India/20170710/3143395.html

- Delhi. 20 Jun 2017. A report by the South Delhi Municipal Corporation (SDMC), shows that between 1 Jan and 17 Jun 2017, 50 cases of dengue were reported, the highest in 4 years. In the same period in 2016, 5 dengue cases were reported. In 2016, a total of 4431 cases of dengue were reported.
http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/chikungunya-dengue-cases-highest-in-4-years/article19106064.ece

- Maharashtra (Mumbai). 13 Jul 2017. 17, 771 cases in 2016 - 2017 265 percent [increase] in Mumbai.
http://www.ndtv.com/mumbai-news/dengue-tuberculosis-cases-on-a-rise-in-mumbai-study-1723998

- Maharashtra (Mumbai). 21 Jun 2017. According to municipal corporation officials, over 2000 people have tested positive for the vector-borne disease with one death. With the outbreak of monsoon rains more and more cases of dengue will be detected and hospitals in Mumbai should be ready to treat them.
http://www.afternoonvoice.com/gruesome-dengue-deaths.html

- Tamil Nadu. 14 Jul 2017. Despite the efforts of civic authorities to prevent vector-borne diseases in the state, the cases of malaria, dengue, filaria, and chikungunya are surging as Tamil Nadu recorded more than 4845 cases of vector-borne diseases, of which 3259 were dengue cases, a surge such that the number of cases reported till May 2017 has outnumbered the total cases reported last year [2016].
http://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/health-and-wellbeing/140717/tamil-nadu-no-2-in-cases-of-vector-borne-diseases-recorded-more-than-4845-cases.html

- Tamil Nadu. 2 Jul 2017. Over 3000 cases reported till the end of May 2017 . Dengue cases reported in the current year [2017] till June end in Tamil Nadu (around 4000 cases) have equaled the total number of cases reported in the state in 2016. While the total number of dengue cases reported in 2016 was 4000, almost same number of cases was reported in a period of 6 months this year [2017]. Most cases were reported from Coimbatore, Tirupur, Theni, Dindigul, Tirunelveli, parts of Tuticorin, Virudhu Nagar, and Kanyakumari districts.
http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/dengue-cases-in-six-months-equalled-total-cases-in-2016/article19197037.ece

- Tamil Nadu (Chennai). 11 Jul 2017. Over 50 dengue cases reported in June 2017. Doctors attribute the spurt in cases to water scarcity and residents storing water in open containers that serve as breeding grounds for the vector.
http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/dengue-rears-its-ugly-head-again-in-city/article19254083.ece

- Kerala. 18 Jul 2017. Dengue has killed at least 21 in Kerala in the last 3 weeks, with more than 11 000 infections, since May [2017]. State buying more hospital beds but there is a shortage of drugs and health-workers.
http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/dengue-in-kerala-21-killed-in-almost-a-month-crisis-looms/story-uiRGD5v8oH4WdpUdInnjOK.html

- Kerala. 27 Jun 2017. 8171 dengue cases confirmed, another 29 582 cases suspected. 14 confirmed deaths, 67 suspected. It is the worst dengue episode to hit the state so far.
http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/kerala-posts-its-worst-dengue-figures/article19152138.ece

- Kerala (Thiruvananthapuram). 18 Jun 2017. 680 suspected dengue cases, of which 138 were tested positive. Also, 11 people died on [Sat 17 Jun 2017], taking the dengue toll in the state to 115 in 2017. Most affected districts: Thiruvananthapuram, Kozhikode, Palakkad. Hospitals overflowing.
http://www.firstpost.com/india/kerala-dengue-outbreak-death-toll-in-2017-rises-to-115-congress-blames-state-govt-3709129.html

- Kerala (Thiruvananthapuram). 16 Jun 2017. On [Fri 16 Jun 2017], the official figures provided by the Health Department's Integrated Disease Surveillance Project showed that 161 confirmed cases were reported in the State, taking the total number of confirmed dengue cases so far this year to 6808. There have been 13 confirmed dengue deaths till date. With over 65 percent of the population seeking care in the private sector, these figures are not indicative. The total number of suspected dengue cases this year so far is an unprecedented 23 091 cases and 38 suspected deaths.
http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/dengue-fever-cases-swell-in-kerala/article19089841.ece

- Kerala (Alappuzha). 3 Jul 2017. A 49-year-old housewife native of Cheriyapathiyoor, Kayamkulam, died of dengue fever in Alappuzha on [Mon 3 Jul 2017]. More than 5 people have lost their lives owing to dengue fever in the past 3 weeks in the district. As many as 225 persons were tested positive of dengue in the district in June [2017]. Most number of cases of dengue were reported at Kayamkulam, Muhamma, Mannancherry, Aryad, Kalavoor, Chettikad, Mararikulam, and Chambakulam.
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/dengue-claims-one-life-in-alappuzha/articleshow/59426367.cms

- Jharkhand (Jamshedpur). 3 Jul 2017. 8 confirmed cases of dengue reported.
http://www.avenuemail.in/jamshedpur/suspected-cases-japanese-encephalitis-surface-jamshedpur/110280/

- Uttar Pradesh. 7 Jul 2017. As many as 89 cases of dengue have been reported in Uttar Pradesh between January and 6 Jul 2017. The bulk of these cases came in June. According to the health department's records, in the same period last year [2016], there were zero dengue cases in the state. Lucknow has topped the chart with 15 cases reported in the city alone.
https://www.nyoooz.com/news/lucknow/860126/89-cases-of-dengue-reported-this-year-in-up/

- Rajasthan (Kota). 17 Jul 2017. 42 patients have tested positive for dengue since January [2017]; 36 cases in July 2017 (in July 2016 only 11). Medical teams are carrying out surveys in affected areas to check the menace.
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/kota-in-dengue-danger-zone-as-36-test-positive-in-july/articleshow/59624228.cms

[Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,142. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Pakistan
- Sindh (Karachi). 6 Jun 2017. At least 11 more dengue fever cases were reported in Karachi city, taking the patients toll to 303 since 1 Jan 2017.
http://dailytimes.com.pk/features/06-Jun-17/more-dengue-cases-emerge-from-karachi

[Maps of Pakistan can be seen at http://pakistanmap.facts.co/pakistanmapof/PakistanAdministrativeMap.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,947. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

China
- Guangdong (Shenzhen). 21 Jun 2017. From 1 Jan to 11 Jun 2017 Shenzhen, where hot and humid weather provides a perfect breeding environment for mosquitoes, saw 17 cases of the insect-transmitted disease. Compared to last year [2016], that's an increase of 54.5 percent.
http://www.thatsmags.com/shenzhen/post/19470/dengue-fever-in-shenzhen

- Yunnan Province. 28 Jun 2017. Xishuangbanna Dai Autonomous Prefecture in southwest China's Yunnan Province has seen a surge in dengue fever cases, with 13 reported since the prefecture's 1st case of this year on [23 Jun 2017]. An emergency response has been launched and measures have been taken for disease prevention and control.
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-06/28/c_136401826.htm

[Maps of China can be seen at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,155. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Laos
- National. 7 Jun 2017. 1760 cases with 3 deaths from January-May 2017. Dengue fever cases recorded in the Lao capital city of Vientiane at a higher rate than other provinces in the country.
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-06/07/c_136346566.htm

[Maps of Laos can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/asia/political-map-of-Laos.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,146. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Myanmar
- National. 17 Jul 2017. 10 101 cases and 54 deaths in the 1st 6 months of 2017. By 12 Jul 2017, there were 2855 dengue cases in Yangon, with 18 reported deaths. Yangon, Ayeyarwady, Rakhine and Mon have seen the highest infection rates since the start of the dengue season.
http://www.elevenmyanmar.com/local/10596

- Yangon. 11 Jul 2017. Surge in children's hospital in the 1st 6 months of 2017, with 1446 cases of dengue fever treated and 7 deaths. From January to 24 Jun 2017, more than 8100 cases were reported and 44 deaths due to dengue across Myanmar.
http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/yangon/26725-dengue-cases-surge-in-yangon-children-s-hospital-in-first-six-months.html

- Yangon. 11 Jun 2017. Between January and [6 Jun 2017], 9 people, including children, died of dengue fever in Yangon, said Dr Khin Nam Lon, the deputy head of the regional Public Health Department. There were 1520 reported dengue cases during that period. 9 out of 141 patients infected with severe dengue fever died. As transmissions rose, the number of 5- and 9-year-olds infected exceeded 500, 10- to 14-year-olds over 300, and over-15s, nearly 100.
http://www.elevenmyanmar.com/local/9968

- Ayeyarwady. 13 Jun 2017. 611 cases, in children in the Ayeyarwady region, with 9 deaths. In 2016, the region recorded 843 dengue cases -- the lowest in recent years; in 2015, there were over 6400 recorded cases. Considering that the rainy season has just begun this year [2017], authorities are worried that the number of dengue cases will continue to take a drastic rise unless precautionary measures are urgently taken. Dengue is most prevalent among children between the ages of 5 and 14. Although the disease does occur year-round, it becomes particularly concerning during the rainy season, which creates prime breeding conditions for mosquitoes.
https://coconuts.co/yangon/news/600-cases-dengue-fever-children-recorded-ayeyarwady-region/

- Rakhine. 8 Jul 2017. Of 1114 people have been infected with dengue haemorrhagic fever (DHF) in Myanmar's Rakhine state, 16 local people died of the disease as of [5 Jul 2017], official media reported [Sat 8 Jul 2017]. The outbreak of DHF was common in Minbya, Kyauktaw, Taungup, and Sittway townships in Rakhine state and people in rural areas are mostly infected with the fever, officials of Rakhine state health department said. About 3304 people have been infected with DHF across the country as of [27 May 2017].
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-07/08/c_136428116.htm

[Maps of Myanmar can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/maps/myanmar_map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,148. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Viet Nam
- National. 10 Jul 2017. 45 074 cases reported with 13 deaths up to [18 Jun 2017]. The number of dengue fever cases reported has increased by 11.3 percent during the 1st 6 months of the year [2017] compared to the same period in 2016, according to the General Department of Preventive Medicine, Ministry of Health, Viet Nam.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/vietnam-dengue-fever-cases-11-percent-2017-date-70516/

- National. 29 Jun 2017. Dengue fever and encephalitis have broken out in Viet Nam earlier than previous years, with many cases of infections and fatalities reported in the capital of Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, and some other localities. In Hanoi's Dong Da urban district, some 500 people have been infected with dengue fever so far this year [2017], nearly 9 times higher than the same period last year [2016], the municipal Preventive Medicine Center said on [Thu 29 Jun 2017], adding that the infections in some other districts increased by 5 to 7 times.
Ho Chi Minh City has reported 329 dengue fever cases in the past 3 weeks, including 3 deaths, with higher infection and fatality rates compared to the same period last year [2016]. According to local preventive medicine centers, the key reason for the surge in dengue fever infections is the early coming of rainy season, which has created favorable conditions for mosquitoes to breed and grow.
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-06/29/c_136403652.htm

- Hanoi. 8 Jun 2017. 1281 cases of dengue fever were recorded in the city by [4 Jun 2017], 2.6 times more than the same period last year [2016].
http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/society/179844/dengue-fever-rises-in-hanoi.html

- Ho Chi Minh City. 9 Jul 2017. A representative of the Hospital for Tropical Diseases reported that the number of patients with dengue fever at the hospital began to increase at the end of May [2017]. The hospital's infectious diseases department, for instance, treated 60 dengue fever inpatients in June [2017], increasing from a monthly average of 40 compared to the last few months. The department does not have space for beds in its rooms and has put beds in hallways.
http://english.vietnamnet.vn/fms/society/181639/provincial-doctors-receive-training-in-dengue-fever-treatment-as-cases-increase.html.

[Maps of Viet Nam can be seen at http://www.onlineasiatravel.com/images/vn/vietnam-map.png and
https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,152. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Philippines
- National. 21 Jun 2017. P1.44 billion [28.4 million USD] worth of dengue vaccines sit idly in storage at the Research Institute for Tropical Medicine -- 3 million doses, despite rise in Dengue cases and deaths. The Department of Health (DOH) had recorded over 200 000 cases of dengue in 2015. By December 2015, the Philippines became the first country in Asia to approve the sale of the vaccine for individuals aged between 9 and 45 years old.
http://news.abs-cbn.com/focus/06/21/17/p14b-dengue-vaccine-undispensed-mired-in-controversy

- Zamboanga City. 23 Jun 2017. Dengue cases for April and May [2017] were significantly higher, registering 130 and 188 cases, respectively, as opposed to 97 and 127 cases reported last year [2016] for the same time period. 90 cases have been reported in June 2017 and to date, 5 deaths have been documented for 2017.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/dengue-cases-zamboanga-city-31517/

- Negros Occidental (Bacolod City). 25 Jun 2017. 376 cases with 5 fatalities from 1 Jan to 10 Jun 2017. The Negros Occidental Provincial Health Office has reported a total of 16 deaths with more than 900 cases from 1 Jan to 17 Jun 2017.
http://reliefweb.int/report/philippines/cho-dengue-victims-bacolod-city-now-5

- Cavite (Trece Martires City). 7 Jul 2017. Dengue-related cases have increased by the month with the reported 1260 cases in the 1st half of 2017. There were 3 official dengue deaths in the 1st 6 months of the year. The dengue case number recorded lately had doubled as compared with the period 1 Jan to 4 Mar 2017, with 647 cases.
http://news.mb.com.ph/2017/07/07/dengue-cases-rising-in-cavite/

[Maps of the Philippines can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/z4y3p5v and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,158. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Malaysia
- National. 4 Jul 2017. Dengue cases have increased by 225 percent in Malaysia since 2013. As of June 2017, there are approximately 48 092 cases and 107 deaths so far.
https://cilisos.my/dengue-shot-up-by-225-in-malaysia-since-2013-why-is-it-that-we-just-cant-beat-dengue/

Maps of Malaysia can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/asia/political-map-of-Malaysian.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,147. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

Thailand
- Chiang Mai. 18 Jul 2017. The northern province of Chiang Mai has seen a large number of people suffering from dengue fever this year [2017], with one confirmed death and 2 other cases pending laboratory test results, a provincial public health office deputy director said on [Tue 18 Jul 2017]. From [1 Jan to 9 Jul 2017], Chiang Mai had 761 dengue fever patients, with the average prevalence rate of 40.77 per 100 000 population.
http://news.thaivisa.com/article/6484/one-confirmed-dead-from-dengue-fever-in-chiang-mai

[Maps of Thailand can be seen at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provinces_of_Thailand and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,4698. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Cambodia
- National. 19 Jul 2017. The number of recorded dengue fever infections in Cambodia dropped dramatically in the 1st half of 2017, when compared to the same period the year before, a health official has said, with deaths due to the virus also dropping. The number of dengue infections in the 1st 24 weeks of the year dropped to 1133, compared to the 2447 in the same period in 2016, according to a statement on the website of the National Centre for Parasitology Entomology and Malaria Control from director Huy Rekol. Spikes and falls of dengue rates tend to follow a predictable cycle, with 2015 and 2016 experiencing higher-than-usual rates.
http://www.phnompenhpost.com/national/dengue-infections-deaths-way-down-govt

[Maps of Cambodia can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/cambodia/maps/cambodia-political-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,145. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Indian Ocean
---
- La Reunion Island. 12 Jul 2017. 11 new cases, 9 only in St Giles-les-Bains, Carosse district. A total of 54 indigenous cases have been confirmed since beginning of the year [2017].
http://www.zinfos974.com/9-nouveaux-cas-de-dengue-rien-que-sur-le-secteur-de-St-Gilles-les-Bains_a116586.html
[in French trans. Corr.SB]

- La Reunion Island. 13 Jun 2017. 40 cases since the beginning of 2017 and 8 imported cases. 8 new locally transmitted cases have been reported or confirmed within the last 15 days. Indian Ocean Cire (Public Health Surveillance/Institut de veille sanitaire, InVS) and the Indian Ocean ARS (Regional health agency. Agence regionale de sante) identified several distinct infected situations, three of which could be related to an imported travel case. 3 communes remain affected by an active circulation of the virus: Saint-Louis/La Palissade district (6 cases), Saint Pierre/Paradise line (6 cases) and Saint Paul/Bois de Nefles (2 cases). The ARS states that the 1st and main focus of the virus, located in Saint-Paul, (18 cases), has not been the subject of new cases in recent weeks. It now appears to be very light or not active. Finally, a few cases have been reported without being clearly linked to one of these known viral circulation zones. This has recently involved two cases, one in Tampon and the other in Plaine des Cafres and for which investigations are under way.
http://www.zinfos974.com/Dengue-40-cas-depuis-le-debut-de-l-annee-8-nouveaux-cas-en-15-jours_a115437.html
[in French trans. Corr.SB]

[Maps of La Reunion Island can be seen at http://www.geoatlas.com/medias/maps/dependencies/Reunion/R35E84U62N01ION/REUNION.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,531. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Pacific
------
- Palau. 13 Jul 2017. 290 cases confirmed, with 106 cases in June [2017]; in April and May [2017], 3 people with pre-existing medical conditions died.
http://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/335064/hundreds-affected-by-dengue-in-palau

[Maps of Palau can be seen at http://www.worldatlas.com/img/areamap/nonav/pwnewz.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,519. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

- New Caledonia. 4 Jul 2017. A 54-year-old man has succumbed to dengue, bringing the death toll to 11 since January [2017]. According to the authorities, nearly 5000 cases have been reported since 1 Sep 2016. The peak of the epidemic was reached in March 2017. The number of clinical cases or suspects has been declining since. With 1970 infected persons, the capital, Noumea, is the most affected by the epidemic, followed by the communes of Paita, Mont-Dore, and Dumbea. All of these cities have recorded the deaths related to dengue, including an infant of 6 months.
https://sivertimes.com/dengue-fever-is-an-eleventh-victim-in-new-caledonia/47572

[Maps of New Caledonia can be seen at https://media1.britannica.com/eb-media/93/3293-004-8AA31F9B.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5190752,43165. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

Africa
---
- Cote d'Ivoire . 8 Jul 2017. According to the Pasteur Institute, the number of patients affected by dengue virus currently stands at 130. Control measures have been hardened.
https://sivertimes.com/dengue-130-confirmed-cases-in-cote-divoire/49342

---
Date: Fri 30 Jun 2017
Source: WHO, Weekly Bulletin on Outbreaks and Other Emergencies. Week 26: 24 - 30 June 2017
http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/255797/1/OEW26-243062017.pdf


- Nigeria. 22 Jun 2017. Single confirmed case reported. WHO awaits further on this possible new event.
- Togo. 18 Jun 2017. 12 confirmed cases reported. WHO awaits further information on this possible new event.
- Cote d'Ivoire. 6 Jun 2017. Of the confirmed cases with further typing completed, 34 cases were identified as dengue virus type 2 and 11 cases as dengue virus type 3. 2/3 of suspected cases were reported from Cocody Commune.
- Kenya. 27 Jun 2017. Outbreak has been reported controlled in Mombasa County (n=991, of which 568 are confirmed) but currently remains active in Wajir County (n=82, of which 51 are confirmed).
- Mauritania. 7 Jun 2017. Single case of dengue hemorrhagic fever confirmed in a traveler from Angola who presented with symptoms of haemorrhaging on 31 May 2017. The case later tested positive for dengue virus infection.

