[2] India (Kerala): 'magical remedies', alert
Date: Thu 29 Jun 2017 09.14 PM IST
Source: Times of India, Times News Network (TNN) [summ., edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thiruvananthapuram/kerala-issues-warning-against-magical-remedies-for-dengue/articleshow/59374075.cms


The directorate of health service has issued a warning against the promotion of drugs which are manufactured unscientifically or unethically claiming to be a remedy for dengue fever. It never spreads through human being but it is spread by the mosquitos, she said. She appealed to the people that no miraculous or magical remedy is available for the dengue fever and hence the people should not become prey at the hands of quacks. It has also to be remembered that people should not have own treatment if they are having dengue or fever.

With the fever cases increasing day-by-day the health department has opened 393 fever clinics across the state. Apart from this 22 mobile fever clinics have also been set up to provide treatment for the people who are unable to reach up to the hospitals in the remotest areas. An additional posting of 80 doctors, 60 staff nurse, 22 pharmacists, and 16 lab technicians have been created to meet the demand. All the hospitals have been asked to conduct medical camps in their neighbouring areas. Meanwhile on [Thu 29 Jun 2017], 27 684 cases of fever were reported from the state, taking the total fever cases reported this year [2017] to [1.428 million]. Today 175 dengue cases were also reported. 2 dengue deaths one each from Malappuram and Thiruvananthapuram were also reported on [Thu 29 Jun 2017].

